I"ã<p>Jessica Marie Johnson is Assistant Professor of History at Michigan State University. Her work has appeared in <em>Slavery &amp; Abolition</em>, <em>The Black Scholar</em>, <em>Meridians: Feminism, Race and Transnationalism</em>, and <em>Debates in the Digital Humanities</em>. As a digital humanist, Johnson explores the way digital and social media disseminate and create historical narratives, in particular, comparative histories of slavery and people of African descent.</p>
